	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=63674'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
<span style='color:#4D7AB0;font-weight:bold; '>Vazaelle_Siderius</span></a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Hero<br>
			
				Posts: 741<br>
				
				Registered: 08-28-2004
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=63674'>







</a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=wizardbalance&message.id=4452#M4452">1</a> of 4
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 233 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		
				background-color: #050A0E; 
				
				 background-image: none;
				 
				background-repeat: repeat-x;
				" 
			>
			<div>Hiya fellow Wizards and other readers of this forum.</div><div> </div><div>This issue has probably been mentioned before. But I just didnt get this out of my mind.</div><div> </div><div>This AA gives us 66% chance to crit for double mana cost of spells. Let me use ACF as example spell. With Prolonged Destruciton you get 1min (correct me if I am wrong) duration of this disc like AA. In one minute we can cast ACF (4.6cast + 2.25 recast = 6.85, lets just say 7sec for realistic number). In 1min one get 8casts.</div><div> </div><div>Assuming that Focuse effect like mana pres is allowed to work on the double mana cost on spells (I have not tested) average manacost on ACF during PD woudl be 1105mana vs 552mana without. Average damage per cast would be 9453 with disc and 6476dmg without.</div><div> </div><div>9453/1105 = 8.55dpm</div><div>6476/552 = 11.73dpm</div><div> </div><div>Assumption is my gear (50% fire focus, 25% fire familiar, 20% MP, 20% spell haste + cleric buff)</div><div> </div><div>Now lets see the difference in dps in the minute with the disc up you do 8x9453 / 60 = 1260dps vs 8x6476 /60 = 863dps<br>The the difference in mana is (8840 vs 4416) 4424mana used. So even with 14k mana you have less than 1/3 left if you use PD.</div><div> </div><div>You gain 46% more dps for 100% more mana cost. And if this fight is not very short you will end up loosing alot of potential damage using this ability.</div><div> </div><div>Comparing to the recent spell EF (9152dmg avg, 1007.5 mana on avg 9dpm, 1220dps chaincasting. using 8060mana)</div><div> </div><div>Okay so I know you can actually use PD with EF... so why not check how that would go. (doing 13100dmg on avg, for 2015mana av per cast, doing 1746dps for 16kmana)</div><div> </div><div> </div><div>Thing is, this disc gives us a small boost in dps for insane amount of mana consumption. This disc is not beneficial in the least it cripple our dps in almost any cases. Only where you would otherwise have mana left at the end of the fight is this really an option. But most fights are long enough so that I get to empty my mana anyway.. and if mob should go down fast and my mana wouldnt I have always EF I could use.. but essentially is the same as ACF with PD.</div><div> </div><div>What would help us in fixing this broken ability would be to change is so that it gave the same boost to crits but did not consume more mana. That way it would be like the discs melee has that they can click when pop and actually gain total damage. And not a situational toy that cripples you most times you try.</div><div> </div><div>And another reason for changing this is that I have all 7vet AA... the 7th is INSANE. Yes its almost overpowering. It gives me like 80% crit rate and no extra mana cost omg!. It lasts 5minutes time aswell. And I often hold 2k dps while this one is going if I chain EF to oom and use Staunch Recovery... mixing in SC5 might actually let me live thru it aswell.</div><div> </div><div>So my point is that FD / PD should be changed to consume no extra mana and give the same ammount of extra crits. And it would become a usefull disc that ppl would use. It lasts short and have a rather long refresh (like everything we got, except TA and TB).</div><div> </div><div>What are you guys thought out there, and do any of you actually use this AA?</div>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							[70 Grand Arcanist] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=664788">Siderius</a> (Gnome) Caer Cadarn
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
